snippet.textDisplay:
I liked the music in this movies, but I don’t know it feels more like Liberal agendas.

I find it annoying how in the movie they make it seem like adapting and assimilating is such a bad thing. The wolves are what majority of humans don’t want to do and it’s evolve and adapt by assimilating to a newer society or a newer outlook of life. They complained and wish to be themselves, but don’t understand how they can still be themselves and still adapt and assimilate to seabrook.

The zombies were looked down on because of how dangerous they were and how different they are. They did right by adapting and finding a way to assimilate yet Zed to it to far by trying to be something who he’s not. Instead of just keeping to who he is yet adapting and assimilating normally.


To me the real lesson is wherever you go, no matter what always learn to adapt, to stimulate to look at different views. Assimilate, and never stay to such one way of thinking, and thinking that it’s ones way or the high way. But I’m the process don’t loose who you are when you began. That’s the real lesson that it should of shown.
